The paper discusses the use of compressed sensing for encryption and security, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-categories. The use of compressed sensing for signal processing and image compression also suggests the multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the practical applications and benefits of compressed sensing, which could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
